{"prompt":"A highly detailed 3D digital illustration of a spherical structure representing a complex multi-layer geodesic architecture. The central sphere is semi-transparent, showing an internal dense geodesic lattice with six floating, non-terminal quantum axes radiating within. The interior geodesic mesh is denser than before, forming a nested fractal-like structural network.

Around the sphere, an expanded external geodesic shell extends outward, also semi-transparent, its triangular tessellations forming multiple concentric layers. This outer shell connects to numerous orbiting satellite nodes in space, each linked by geodesic struts, creating a vast external mesh. The overall impression is of geodesic-within-geodesic-within-geodesic layers, nested and interconnected.

No text anywhere in the image. The style is clean, modern, luminous, emphasizing structural complexity, transparency, and quantum adjacency. The axes inside should appear floating, without obvious beginnings or ends.","size":"1024x1024","n":1}
